course_description: This course examines the interrelationships among embryonic development, structure, function, and zoogeography of vertebrates with a focus on phylogenies and connections with humans. Laboratories include a morphological analysis of major vertebrate taxa.
prerequisites: (BIOL 142 and BIOL 142L) or BIOL_OX 142WE or equivalent transfer credit as a prerequisite.
